
### `.gitignore`
This file tells Git which files or directories to ignore. It's important to exclude sensitive information (like API keys, virtual environments, or system-specific files) from being pushed to GitHub.

```gitignore
# Python specific
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
__pycache__/

# Flask specific
instance/
*.db
*.sqlite3

# Virtual environment
venv/
env/
.venv/
.env/

# IDE/editor files
.idea/
.vscode/

# MacOS specific
.DS_Store

# Windows specific
Thumbs.db
